  {
    "title": "Absolutely worth a visit!",
    "rating": 5,
    "travelDate": "2024-09",
    "publishedDate": "2024-09-27",
    "text": "We arrived just in time for feeding, which only happens every few weeks. What a spectacle! We were greeted very nicely and after we were the only visitors at that time, the owner took a lot of time for the tour. We didn't think the farm would be so big and the tour so interesting. We learned many new, interesting facts about the crocodiles and also some myths were clarified. The day before, one of the guides on the Chobe River told us that parts of crocodiles were poisonous, but that's not true at all! We can definitely recommend the visit!",
    "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g297318-d12948270-r971655959-Chobe_Crocodile_Farm-Kasane_Chobe_National_Park_North_West_District.html",
